g.text: - Send audio to API, convert it to text and send it to an LLM
- Collect LLM's reply, convert it to audio and send back to client
- Play API's response automatically as soon as the request resolves
- Needs to connect with 3rd party LLM agent
- Needs to convert speech to text to talk to LLM, then convert answer to audio back to us
- Needs minimal control to record audio: start, stop
- Needs control to silence the LLM answer: pause audio
- Security capabilities: user auth and api key authorization
- Scalability: since we are building a PoC, we don't need to design at scale
- Storage: we are not storing any data in this PoC
- Fault Tolerance: we might run into errors if the LLM service is out
- audioInput - audio file generated on client side
- audioOutput - audio file generated from LLMs answer
